<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="87" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1660,2009]" pageId="10" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1911,1937]" pageId="10" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Deyrolle" authorityYear="1864" box="[325,499,1911,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis box="[325,499,1911,1937]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="87">Agrilus vittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the larger species (
<quantity box="[856,996,1910,1937]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="10" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.5 mm</quantity>
) with pubescent perisutural stripes on elytra and with subangulate elytral apices. The species is distinctive by reduced membranous sensory zones of the parameres and by widely rounded apex of medial lobe (penis) (
<figureCitation box="[859,950,1982,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 4" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1894,1919]" captionTargetBox="[156,1435,196,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1435,196,1859]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 4A–4F. Dry preserved aedeagus, habitus and ovipositor mounted in DMHF of Agrilus. Aedeagus. 4A, A. viridicupreus Saunders, 1866; 4B, A. viridifrons Kerremans, 1893; 4D, A. vittatus Deyrolle, 1864; 4E A. yunnanicola Obenberger, 1936. Ovipositor. 4F, A. viridifrons Kerremans, 1893; Habitus and aedeagus of holotype. 4C, A. fulvovittatus Fisher, 1921." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3268311/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="87">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
